Only one larva was found, on 14.6 . On 9.7 . the full grown larva ( 6 th instar) was photographed (
Fig. 22
). On the evening of the same day it stopped feeding, emptied its gut (with no extra moult) and thereafter walked slowly and incessantly, seeking a place to pupate. It was dry-prepared by blowing air into the empty skin, and although this did not succeed very well, the original colours remained.
